---
description: Tenant safety architecture enforcement
alwaysApply: true
---

CephasOps enforces strict tenant isolation.

Rules:

• Tenant-owned writes must occur inside a valid tenant scope
• TenantScopeExecutor is the standard execution boundary
• TenantSafetyGuard protects persistence
• CompanyId must be propagated for tenant-owned jobs/events/webhooks

Reject solutions that:

• write tenant-scoped entities without tenant context
• silently fallback from tenant scope to platform bypass
• bypass TenantSafetyGuard

Before implementation, determine:

1. Tenant or platform execution
2. Executor method required
3. Null-company behavior
4. Required tests
